messages.message:
*Cypress weekly update*
• :white_check_mark: `file-list.spec.ts` From last week (can’t find selector “[data-testgroup^=REVIEW_LIST_FILE_CONTAINER]“) fixed by https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/65711
• :white_check_mark: `aihub-derived-field.spec.ts` was failing because live test didn’t wait for debounce before clicking “Run all” button. Fixed with new debounce “run immediately” callback  (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/65708)which the live test now invokes via the enter key instead of clicking “Run all”.
• :white_check_mark: `run-app.spec.ts` was failing due to backend issue related to checking org tier, fixed by https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/65884
• :white_check_mark: `loginless-sample-results` showing “you do not have access to this app” (also affects `run-public-app.spec.ts`) moved to non-blocking for now ~but should be fixed soon (https://instabase.slack.com/archives/CSY11CK7T/p1733432399620919?thread_ts=1733424839.667839&cid=CSY11CK7T)~ & is now fixed
• :question: `downstream-integrations.spec.ts` failing due to too many db connections (https://instabase.slack.com/archives/CSY11CK7T/p1733518292748369?thread_ts=1733437244.441529&cid=CSY11CK7T), may need to move to non-blocking if not resolved soon.
• :x:`converse-app.spec.ts` failing on `uploads, digitizes, deletes, and displays the files correctly`, not fixed yet but moved to non-blocking for now

Jag’s fix was merged and deployed, so `loginless-sample-results` and `run-public-app` are passing in CI now! example run (https://cloud.cypress.io/projects/cfhedy/runs/16188/test-results?actions=%5B%5D&browsers=%5B%5D&groups=%5B%5D&isFlaky=%5B%5D&modificationDateRange=%7B%22startDate%22:%221970-01-01%22,%22endDate%22:%222038-01-19%22%7D&orderBy=EXECUTION_ORDER&oses=%5B%5D&specs=%5B%7B%22label%22:%22apps/src/aihub/__e2e__/ViewApp/loginless-sample-results.spec.ts%22,%22value%22:%22%5B%5C%22c9e6d40b-396e-458e-b195-f7dd670c4cd2%5C%22,%5C%22156d3fb8-c7ac-44ac-b13e-56949e3014ee%5C%22%5D%22%7D,%7B%22label%22:%22apps/src/aihub/__e2e__/ViewApp/run-public-app.spec.ts%22,%22value%22:%22%5B%5C%226b67addb-41f7-440f-85f0-a80d5d614f01%5C%22,%5C%22196a70f9-5c6c-4c22-8a79-270019fe2ec0%5C%22%5D%22%7D%5D&statuses=%5B%5D&testingTypesEnum=%5B%5D)

so we should move them back to blocking
